{"id":"6346","name":"Contact Anniversaries","tagline":"Add events for contact anniversaries","icon":"ios15 c4292093695 g59681","latest":"31869","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"Contact Anniversaries Banner\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/XgRZy75.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Made for Contacts\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/aJCeyUH.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"Made for Calendar\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/vSNaDmc.jpg\"></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>This shortcut will search your contacts to find any that have an anniversary date listed then add it to your calendar as an all-day recurring event. </p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> this shortcut requires the <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/scriptable/id1405459188\">Scriptable</a> app to create the recurring events. </p>\n<h5>Instructions</h5>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Make sure you have contacts with an \"anniversary\" date item assigned to them. Otherwise the search will produce no results</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run the shortcut and select from the options\n<img alt=\"Main Menu\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/7QkVWZF.jpg\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add Anniversary Events To Calendar<ul>\n<li>On import/first run, you will be prompted to select a calendar to add the events to. It is recommended to create a new calendar to do this but it is entirely up to your choice. In order for calendars to appear in this list of choices there has to be an event within the next 90 days on the calendar <strong>NOTE: this time window is no longer valid in v1.5+</strong>\n<img alt=\"anniversary calendar\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/EMVDG62.jpg\"></li>\n<li>After the shortcut finishes searching, it will show you a quicklook window with the names of the contacts for which events were created or removed</li>\n<li>If no contacts or events are found, you will be notified of this in the same window</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Remove Anniversary Events<ul>\n<li>The shortcut will search for events created by the shortcut and confirm you want to remove them</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Reset Settings<ul>\n<li>The shortcut will prompt you to erase the settings file then will run the shortcut again to get setup</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img alt=\"End Screens - no events\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/gysywCe.jpg\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"End Screens - added event\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/NYi1l9T.png\"></p>\n<p>Shoutout to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>ROP for MediaKit used to make this page</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>D3W10 for SwingE used in the shortcut</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.5 - Feb. 17, 2022, 10:11 a.m.</strong></p><p>Version 1.5 Release Notes<br>- Changed the setup of the Calendar name to not need an event on the desired calendar to be able to find it<br><br>- Total Actions: #0<br>- Created on iOS 15.3.1<br>- Released at Feb 17, 2022</p>"}